Rob Griffin

I am a programmer with professional experience with R (over 10 years) and SAS, training in R, SAS, Java and Kotlin, and self-study and hobbyist experience with Python, HTML, CSS and JavaScript among others. I enjoy practising coding with personal activities regularly involving data projects (example), mobile app development, contributing to Stackoverflow and web development projects (including this page, built using a mix of R, RMarkdown, HTML, CSS and JavaScript read how I made it here).

I completed my PhD in Evolutionary Genetics in 2015 before moving onto postdoctoral positions in Finland, Sweden and Australia. In 2020, I decided that academia not the path for me and chose to pursue a career in programming - I chose to pursue programming as this was a very enjoyable area of my academic work and I had a platform of skills that I could build upon. I continue to learn and practice programming languages in my free time, along with spending time with my three young children (Nils, Olof and Sven) and partner (Anna), getting out into the forest for berry and mushroom picking, cycling and running.

I am looking for programming work in Gothenburg or the Vnersborg/Trollhttan area and within a company where solving problems with high-quality and creative code is the primary goal. While I have a strong background in data science and statistical programming, I am very keen to exploring new areas of programming where I can learn how the languages I have been learning (particularly Java, Kotlin and Python) are used in a real-world context. Opportunities for technical training and progression into leadership are also desirable.
